<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
1</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>   
Blessed is the man that walketh not in the counsel of the ungodly, nor standeth 
in the way of sinners, nor sitteth in the seat of the scornful.</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>But his delight is in the   
law of YHVH; and in his law doth he meditate day and night.</P></TD></TR><TR>   
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>And he shall be like a tree     
planted by the rivers of water, that bringeth forth his fruit in his season;    
his leaf also shall not wither; and whatsoever he doeth shall prosper.</P></TD> 
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>The ungodly are not    
so: but are like the chaff which the wind driveth away.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Therefore the ungodly shall not     
stand in the judgment, nor sinners in the congregation of the righteous.</P>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>For YHVH knoweth  
the way of the righteous: but the way of the ungodly shall perish.</P></TD></TR>
